<subSubSection id="8950485EDB6D62D488160321DB241019" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="2628E33540D54472E3696DF399932CD0" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5ADDA0919C9B5590A3F17640602C9121" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Trees to about 7 m tall with subtetragonal, stems stellate pubescent apically, glabrous to glabrescent with age; the nodal line present. Leaves of a pair equal to somewhat unequal in length. Petiole 1-5 cm. Leaf blades 4-15.5 
<normalizedToken id="549FDDF97E07B330234D029694A1948D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.1-7 cm, 3-nerved, elliptic, the base obtuse, the apex obtuse, acute or acuminate, the margin entire or weakly crenulate-dentate near the apex, the adaxial surface glabrous, the abaxial surface glabrous except for tuft domatia of stipitate branching hairs present at the base of the leaf and minute puncticulate glands throughout the surface. Inflorescence a terminal panicle 5-17.7 cm long branched above the base, rachis flattened accessory branches absent or present, bracts and bracteoles linear, 2-3 mm long, deciduous or appearing absent. Pedicels 5-12 mm. Flowers 6 merous, calyptrate. Floral buds 11-18 
<normalizedToken id="2BCFF9030199DEC02F68EFF0D50554EA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, elliptic pyriform, the base rounded, apex acuminate and apiculate, slightly constricted in the middle, the hypanthium 4-5 
<normalizedToken id="9ED800E49289473296E7B7EF6A7C5A29" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-5.25 mm, glabrous and ribbed. Petals 10-14 
<normalizedToken id="8DCC9145EBC13DD0C79F333C445075CB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 mm, white or pinkish white, obtriangular, spreading, emarginate, glabrous. Stamens (17-)18(-20), 6-7.5 mm long, the filaments 3.5-4 mm long, reportedly yellow, anthers 3.5-4 
<normalizedToken id="1E95D8A6F3586FF9B48F075ADCEFE96B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1 mm, linear, yellow, slightly laterally compressed, the pore ca. 0.2 mm wide, terminal. Ovary (5-)6(-7) locular, inferior, the apex glabrous and elevated into a conspicuous collar around the style. Style 7-8 mm long, bending below the stigma, vertical and horizontal distance from the anthers to the stigma absent; stigma, punctate, ca. 0.5 mm wide. Dry berry 7-9 
<normalizedToken id="E35C3FFD5AA5AD385FA77207307681DC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-9 mm. Seeds 0.5-0.75 mm, ovoid to pyramidal, the testa angulate and smooth to slightly roughened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2569C5D290A3897B4EA639359817A47F" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2F75F1F1C090A115B60C3453CC29DEF1" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2C856637BD3379A61778B7760DB98C9" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A507C84CDCFEB0A9E4B66969C38048B3" captionStart="Figure 99" captionStartId="F99" captionText="Figure 99. Distribution of Conostegia procera." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure99" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96457" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">99</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Jamaica, 500-1300 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="37B8666746363BE713B9474B697CE266" ID-Zenodo-Dep="974239" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure99" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96457" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" start="Figure 99" startId="F99">
<paragraph id="5CF7F54BE8E0CCE80B6DF0E6815AB0FD" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="60A702F8BCE2FB1353ED7D50968FC7DD" bold="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Figure 99.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="5768239D3C168C48EF55B2F1FB6F861C" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="C2DA7476C9F7B2D88F7B7D6DFFE523FA" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="D4ABCE4A367EA9A3059971DF659E7046" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="60FB91E0EC18EA5BFDD20A3946117183" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="F883440F5DA148ADE86EBAE28220E962" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its leaves with mite domatia, usually white flowers, and ribbed hypanthium. 
<bibRefCitation id="3A8998338ADB2241B3FDF5EA448E9059" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
found this species does not overlap in flowering time with the other Jamaican endemics. 
<bibRefCitation id="CF7AF0CE3D8A511335FC15D6394C45C4" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
thought 
<taxonomicName id="07208BDB59D4285E5DC419F5B2938D9F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="C406C790ABD28AF0565A9AE2C09B9AFF" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
highly resembled 
<taxonomicName id="BE8B75F293D9FEA21EF62421EEB7BEAB" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jaliscana" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaliscana">
<emphasis id="BE8F0F605DF1CB7AC1DED800F7C79C10" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia jaliscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placed it in a section together with the rest of Jamaican endemics. The molecular phylogeny places both Jamaican endemics sampled (including 
<taxonomicName id="5CE2FDF731DF85DEA170C49B384407B1" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia procera" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="E06208BA4ADCBCD5B7153FA7F4FCAA5F" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) forming a well supported clade and belonging to a clade that also includes 
<taxonomicName id="A8C12BC67E311DFC09ECACD742AD303E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1850" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia rufescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis id="6ED5B62D9F07BF6D4259E3F159EAE902" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9C04069CB11853A17FF9BAFCC7520440" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Gleason" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia cuatrecasii" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuatrecasii">
<emphasis id="C21903E23EAA875A00AD6BBE3CF3B3FA" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia cuatrecasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="49F484674F5DE989054D53D60A2958FF" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jaliscana" order="Myrtales" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaliscana">
<emphasis id="9F277FA41E02FC7CE6D1015C838927EB" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Conostegia jaliscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the other hand falls with species of the giant stigma clade, which is centered in Central America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
